Eg Message:  BOY

Encryption

ASCII VALUE OF B= 66, O=79, Y=89 

ASCII value of B   to binary is 01000010

		O to binary is   01001111

		Y to binary is 01011001

So BOY will become 01000010	01001111	01011001

After DNA Combination substitution it will become CAAG    CATT     CCGC

256 DNA Combination to extended ASCII value substitution let it be @#% from the substitution table. So the final encrypted message is @#%

Our system, encrypts a plain text file and outputs file called as <original filename until a dot> _en.txt
Decryption output is also in a file called <encrypt file name without _en> _dc.txt



Decryption


DECRYPTION OF TEXT

Step 1:. Encrypted text to random key of ACTG combination based on Public key
Step 2 :. ACTG combination to binary
Step 3:. Binary to ASCII value
Step 4:. ASCII value to Message

@		#		%

Encrypted message to random key generated value CAAG     	        CATT   	         CCGC

Combination to binary 				    01000010	      01001111	         01011001
Binary to ASCII value	  66	 79	 89
Back to message 	  B	  O	  Y


